               <msContents>
                  <summary>An account, in verse, of the birth and life of the prophet<persName key="n 79062738" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/66440309/">Zoroaster</persName>, by Zartusht Bahram Pazhdu, the author of<title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Ardāvīrāfnāmah</title>in verse and<title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">Dāstān-i Jingihir Nighājah</title>(Persian MS 301). The title is given in the Manuscript on folio<locus from="1v" to="1v">1v</locus>as<title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Mawlūd-i Zartusht</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa">مولود زرتشت</title>The same is also given in the text on folio<locus from="61v" to="61v">61v</locus>چو مولود زرتشت خوانی تمام / بدل کن برو آفرینی تمام . The same title is also given in the author’s other work,<title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Jingihir Nighājah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa">جنگهر نگهاچه</title>(Persian 301), where he states that his mother used to read to him two works (daftar), the Mawlūd-i Zartusht and the Ardā-yī vīrāf دو دفتر بود نقل اندر بر من کتابی بود زان مولود زرتشت درو چیزی که بد مقصود زرتشت. The beginning of this Manuscript corresponds with that in Sachau/Ethe (British Library) and to some extent to that in Rieu (British Museum), but is different from that in Ethe (10):</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_300-item1">
                     <author key="2008034018 " ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/77486993">Zartusht Bahrām, active 1278زرتشت بهرام پژدو‏<addName xml:lang="ar" type="laqab"/>
                        <addName xml:lang="ar" type="kunyah"/>
                        <addName xml:lang="ar" type="khitab"/>
                        <addName xml:lang="ar" type="nisbah"/>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Zartushtnāmah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">Zartusht nāmah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa">زرتشت نامه</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" type="alt"/>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="desc"/>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar" type="beginning">سخن را بنام خدای جهان بآغاز<sic>بیاغاز</sic>در آشکار و نهان</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar"/>
                     <listBibl>
